        </div>

        <p>The hovalin is a functional acoustic violin that can be produced using most standard consumer 3d printers. The total cost of raw materials for a Hovalin (4/4) is currently about $70.  The hovalin was designed with <a href="fusion360.autodesk.com" target="_blank">Autodesk Fusion 360</a>. It's shape and dimensions are inspired by the stradivarius violin model.</p>

        <strong><p>There are three ways to get in on this: </p></strong>
      </div>
    </div>
